This is the README for PangoConst version 0.03.

PangoConst is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language, a
library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document contains
four sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

PangoConst - the Pango constants without Glib / Gtk2

This module copies the PANGO_* constants from "Gtk2::Pango" so that
you can use them without having to import/install the whole of Glib
and Gtk2.

Don't ask me what the PANGO_* constants are doing in Gtk2 rather than
in "Pango" itself. A quote from Gtk2::Pango's documentation: "This
module shouldn't exist".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following
websites:

    * http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?PangoConst
    * http://metacpan.org/release/PangoConst

(These links go to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your
computer using

    perldoc PangoConst

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

This module requires Perl version 5.6.1 or later.

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan PangoConst

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm PangoConst

To install the module from the source file, PangoConst-0.03.tar.gz, follow
this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz PangoConst-0.03.tar.gz
    cd PangoConst-0.03
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can
report a bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/pangoconst/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of PangoConst, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/pangoconst>. 

